    "full": "siemensiiA. albersdoerferiA. lithographica|synonyms = See text|location = Europe|height = 0.5 meters|weight = 0.8-1 kilogram (1.8-2.2 pounds)|length = 500 millimeters (20 inches)|diet = Carnivorous}}Archaeopteryx is an extinct genus of archaeopterygid dinosaur that lived in Europe during the Late Jurassic. ==Description== Archaeopteryx had large feathers on its arms, tail and legs used for gliding or flying short distances. Archaeopteryx was once thought to be the earliest bird, but the discoveries of Anchiornis, Xiaotingia, Aurornis and Asteriornis proved that Archaeopteryx wasn't the oldest bird."
