    "short": "|name_meaning = Horn lizard|species = See text|synonyms = Megalosaurus nasicornis|location = North America and Africa|height = 2.5-3m (8-10ft)|weight = 1-2 tons|length = 16-20 feet (5-6 meters)|diet = Carnivorous}}Ceratosaurus is an extinct genus of ceratosaurian theropod dinosaur that lived in North America during the Late Jurassic.",
    "full": "== Description == Ceratosaurus is famous for being the only large theropod with a singular nasal crest. This structure was probably used completely for display. Combined with the large lacrimal crests, these would have made the animal look more dangerous, and accordingly more intimidating. Evidence for the idea they were used for display comes in the form of a juvenile Ceratosaurus skull known to have had smaller lacrimal and nasal crests than the adults. This clearly demonstrates the fact that the crests developed as the animal matured, reinforcing the idea they were used for displays."
