    "img": "https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/prehistoric-wiki/images/1/1b/Guanlong.jpg",
    "short": "}}Guanlong is an extinct genus of proceratosaurid tyrannosauroid that lived in China during the Late Jurassic.",
    "full": "== Description == Guanlong is currently represented by two specimens, one adult and another immature. Guanlong bore a large curved crest on its head, which was brittle. Unlike the later tyrannosaurs that descended from Guanlong, the animal had three digits on each hand. Guanlong would have bore a striking resemblance to Dilong, likely covered in a coat of primitive feathers, aside from the distinguishing head crest. Thee holotype specimen is a partially complete adult, and the affiliated paratype is an immature, nearly complete and articulate skeleton.",
